1. The best quiche Florentine (spinach and gruyere) recipe: 
1 blind baked pâte brisée shell (a good bake)
Sweat 1 large shallot, finely diced, in 1 tablespoon of butter for a couple of minutes.
Add ½ pound spinach and 1 teaspoon of salt and cook for 1 to 2 minutes until wilted.
Cool spinach on paper towel lined sheet tray.
Make custard: heat together ½ cup milk and ½ cup heavy cream just until simmering. Whisk into 3 eggs, and then whisk vigorously adding 6 grams fine salt, a pinch of ground white pepper and a few gratings of nutmeg. 
Layer 1/3 cup grated gruyere, 1/3 spinach mix, ½ custard, followed by 1/3 cup grated gruyere, 1/3 spinach mix and remaining custard. Top with 1/3 cup grated gruyere and remaining spinach mix.
Bake at 325F for 40 to 50 minutes until custard is set.

I had an absolutely fantastic weekend in Lambertville, NJ. One of my favorite moments was meeting Aki and Alex @ideasinfood and eating their delicious doughnuts @curiositydoughnuts in Furlong, PA. Kindred spirits in food. I frequently get wrapped up in my own bubble in Brooklyn, and this weekend was a nice reminder to get out, slow down a bit, and breathe.

I had an amazing week cycling in Mallorca with a group of incredible and strong women! I learned so much about myself. And I became a more confident rider, became less fearful of descending, embraced my love of ascending, and gained lots of group riding skills. Plus I got to do all of this in beautiful Mallorca. This trip really opened the door of possibility for me with cycling both at home and out in the world. I’m now dreaming of trips where I can combine travel, cycling, and of course, food! 

Thank you @girlsgetstrongcycling for this amazing experience! ❤️

I’m so happy to help kickoff the new season of @cherrybombe ‘s baking podcast with @jessiesheehanbakes ! We deep dived into how to make babka, and I had a blast! ❤️ Link in my stories.

Sending love to my friend (and the best physical therapist ever!) @sammyjacobsen on her marriage to Ryan today. I’m so happy I could share in your celebration by making your cake. ❤️ The cake is a cardamom cake (single origin baraka green cardamom from @diasporaco) with a cardamom milk syrup soak, kumquat jam, orange honey ricotta mousse, and vanilla bean buttercream.
